  "local_port": 49374,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Why do I get snapchat notifications of some people but not others?",
  "response": "Experiencing inconsistent Snapchat notifications\u2014receiving alerts from some friends but not others\u2014can be frustrating. Several factors might contribute to this issue. Below are the most common reasons and steps you can take to resolve them:\n\n### 1. **App Notification Settings**\n\n**Within Snapchat:**\n- **Check Notification Preferences:**\n  1. Open Snapchat and tap on your profile icon in the top-left corner.\n  2. Tap the gear icon (\u2699\ufe0f) to access **Settings**.\n  3. Scroll down to **Notifications**.\n  4. Ensure that **All Notifications** are enabled. You can also customize specific notification types (e.g., **Chat Notifications**, **Story Notifications**, etc.) to suit your preferences.\n\n**Device-Level Settings:**\n- **iOS:**\n  1. Go to **Settings** > **Notifications** > **Snapchat**.\n  2. Ensure that **Allow Notifications** is toggled on.\n  3. Check that alerts are allowed on the Lock Screen, Notification Center, and as Banners.\n  \n- **Android:**\n  1. Go to **Settings** > **Apps** or **Applications** > **Snapchat** > **Notifications**.\n  2. Ensure that notifications are enabled.\n  3. Check individual notification categories (e.g., **Chat**, **Story**) and make sure they're active.\n\n### 2. **Individual Friend Settings**\n\n- **Muted Conversations:**\n  - If you've muted specific friends or groups, you won't receive notifications from them.\n  - To check:\n    1. Open Snapchat and swipe right to go to the **Chat** screen.\n    2. Find the conversation you suspect is muted.\n    3. Tap and hold on the conversation and see if the **Mute Notifications** option is enabled. If so, disable it.\n\n- **Friends Who Have Muted You:**\n  - If certain friends have muted you, you won't receive notifications when they send snaps or chats. This is something beyond your control, but you can verify by attempting to reconnect or communicate through other means.\n\n### 3. **App and System Glitches**\n\n- **Update Snapchat:**\n  - Ensure you're using the latest version of Snapchat. Outdated versions can have bugs affecting notifications.\n  - Visit the **App Store** (iOS) or **Google Play Store** (Android) to check for updates.\n\n- **Restart Your Device:**\n  - Sometimes, simply restarting your phone can resolve temporary glitches affecting notifications.\n\n- **Reinstall Snapchat:**\n  - If problems persist, try uninstalling and reinstalling the app. This can fix corrupted files or settings that might be causing issues.\n  - **Note:** Ensure you remember your login credentials before doing this, and consider backing up any important data.\n\n### 4. **Network and Data Issues**\n\n- **Stable Internet Connection:**\n  - Snapchat requires a stable internet connection to deliver notifications. Ensure you're connected to Wi-Fi or have a reliable mobile data signal.\n\n- **Battery Optimization Settings:**\n  - Some devices have battery-saving features that restrict background data for apps, which can delay or prevent notifications.\n  \n  - **iOS:**\n    - Generally less restrictive, but ensure **Low Power Mode** is not limiting app activity.\n\n  - **Android:**\n    1. Go to **Settings** > **Battery** > **Battery Optimization**.\n    2. Find **Snapchat** and set it to **Not Optimized** to allow it to run in the background.\n\n### 5. **Privacy Settings**\n\n- **Who Can Contact You:**\n  - Snapchat has settings that control who can send you snaps or chats. If certain friends are restricted or blocked, you won't receive notifications from them.\n  \n  - To check:\n    1. Open Snapchat and go to **Settings**.\n    2. Tap on **Blocked** to see if any friends are inadvertently blocked.\n    3. Review **Who Can...** sections to ensure your settings allow friends to contact you.\n\n### 6. **Account Issues**\n\n- **Snapchat Server Problems:**\n  - Sometimes, Snapchat's servers might be experiencing issues, leading to delayed or missing notifications.\n  - Check websites like [Downdetector](https://downdetector.com/status/snapchat/) to see if others are reporting similar problems.\n\n- **Account Verification:**\n  - Ensure your account is verified and in good standing. Issues like violations of Snapchat's terms of service can affect functionality.\n\n### 7. **Interaction Levels**\n\n- **Algorithmic Prioritization:**\n  - Snapchat, like many social platforms, may prioritize notifications based on your interaction levels with friends. If you frequently interact with certain friends, their notifications might appear more reliably.\n  \n  - To increase interactions:\n    - Send regular snaps or chats to the friends you want to receive notifications from.\n    - View their Stories and engage with their content.\n\n### **Troubleshooting Checklist**\n\n1. **Verify Settings:**\n   - Both within Snapchat and your device's notification settings.\n\n2. **Update the App:**\n   - Ensure you\u2019re using the latest version.\n\n3. **Check Internet Connection:**\n   - Make sure you have a stable connection.\n\n4. **Restart or Reinstall:**\n   - Try restarting your device or reinstalling Snapchat.\n\n5. **Review Friend-specific Settings:**\n   - Ensure you haven't muted or blocked friends unintentionally.\n\n6. **Check for Server Issues:**\n   - Look for any widespread Snapchat outages.\n\nIf you've tried all the above steps and are still experiencing issues, consider reaching out to [Snapchat Support](https://support.snapchat.com/) for further assistance. They can provide more personalized help based on your account and device specifics.",
